comment15.target=boolean\ isLidded()
comment15.text=\r\n\ Checks\ if\ the\ cup\ has\ a\ lid\ paired\r\n\ \r\n\ @return\ true\ if\ the\ cup\ has\ a\ lid,\ false\ otherwise\r\n
comment16.params=
comment16.target=Lid\ getPairedLid()
comment16.text=\r\n\ Returns\ the\ paired\ lid\r\n\ \r\n\ @return\ The\ paired\ Lid\ object,\ or\ null\ if\ not\ paired\r\n
comment17.params=id
comment17.target=int\ calculateHeight(int)
comment17.text=\r\n\ Calculates\ the\ height\ of\ a\ cup\ based\ on\ its\ id\r\n\ Height\ formula\:\ 2^(idNumC-1)\r\n\ Examples\:\ idNumC\=1\ \u2192\ 2^0\=1,\ idNumC\=2\ \u2192\ 2^1\=2,\ idNumC\=3\ \u2192\ 2^2\=4,\ idNumC\=4\ \u2192\r\n\ 2^3\=8\r\n\ \r\n\ @param\ idNumC\ The\ cup\ identifier\r\n\ @return\ The\ calculated\ height\r\n
comment18.params=idNumC
comment18.target=java.lang.String\ getColorForId(int)
comment18.text=\r\n\ Assigns\ a\ unique\ color\ based\ on\ the\ cup's\ id\r\n\ Colors\ cycle\ through\ the\ array\ if\ there\ are\ many\ cups\r\n\ \r\n\ @param\ idNumC\ The\ cup\ identifier\r\n\ @return\ The\ color\ as\ a\ String\r\n
comment19.params=tower
comment19.target=boolean\ canEnterTower(Tower)
comment19.text=\r\n\ Determines\ whether\ this\ cup\ is\ allowed\ to\ enter\ the\ tower.\r\n\ Each\ cup\ subtype\ defines\ its\ own\ entry\ condition.\r\n\r\n\ @param\ tower\ the\ Tower\ this\ cup\ is\ trying\ to\ enter\r\n\ @return\ true\ if\ the\ cup\ can\ be\ pushed\ onto\ the\ tower\r\n
comment2.params=
comment2.target=int\ getId()
comment2.text=\r\n\ Returns\ the\ cup's\ identifier\r\n\ \r\n\ @return\ The\ cup\ idNumC\r\n
comment20.params=tower
comment20.target=void\ onPush(Tower)
comment20.text=\r\n\ Defines\ the\ insertion\ behavior\ when\ this\ cup\ is\ pushed\ onto\ the\ tower.\r\n\ Each\ cup\ subtype\ decides\ how\ it\ adds\ itself\ to\ the\ stack.\r\n\r\n\ @param\ tower\ the\ Tower\ this\ cup\ is\ being\ pushed\ onto\r\n
comment21.params=tower
comment21.target=boolean\ canBeRemoved(Tower)
comment21.text=\r\n\ Determines\ whether\ this\ cup\ is\ allowed\ to\ be\ removed\ from\ the\ tower.\r\n\ Each\ cup\ subtype\ defines\ its\ own\ removal\ condition.\r\n\r\n\ @param\ tower\ the\ Tower\ this\ cup\ is\ in\r\n\ @return\ true\ if\ the\ cup\ can\ be\ removed\ from\ the\ tower\r\n
